arch:property.oc:show_val: Arbitrary spit through the midden deposit that is similar to the other units analysed. Flotation sample 6 was fully recorded so that the taphonomic information could be compared with other units from the same midden. The rest of the material was recorded for diagnostics only. NR 2001: F119 is a fragment of a bone ring. NR 2006: A bird specimen was returned from microfauna, from Sample 5 >4mm flotation 100% sorted.

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
